7 An Act relating to schools; directing the State
Department of Education to develop curriculum
8 resources related to the atrocities of communism;
mandating the atrocities of communism be taught in
9 grades six through twelve; specifying requirements
for the manner of teaching; directing the State
10 Department of Education to develop professional
learning opportunities; defining communism; providing
11 for codification; and providing an effective date.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 11-103.17 of Title 70, unless
17 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. The State Department of Education, in consultation with
19 experts in political history, human rights, and the history of
20 communism, shall develop, and make available to public schools,
21 resources related to the atrocities of communism for grade-
22 appropriate instruction of students in grades six through twelve.
23 B. Beginning in the 2026-2027 school year, the atrocities of
24 communism shall be taught to students in grades six through twelve
Req. No. 10430 Page 1

1 in p ublic schools in this state, as prescribed in the Oklahoma
2 Academic Standards. This instruction may be integrated into one or
3 more existing courses of study and shall be taught in a manner that:
4 1. Fosters an understanding of the causes, rise, and
5 consequences of communist regimes, including the historical context
6 of hostile takeovers and political revolutions;
7 2. Explores the human cost of communism, including the
8 systematic slaughter, imprisonment, and oppression of individuals,
9 as well as the loss of basic freedoms and human rights;
10 3. Examines the effects of communism on societies, economies,
11 and cultures, highlighting the destruction of social and economic
12 structures under such regimes;
13 4. Promotes dialogue on the advantages and protections afforded
14 to Americans through the principles of the United States’
15 constitutional republic political structure, including individual
16 liberties, property rights, and the rule of law; and
17 5. Develops critical thinking about political systems,
18 encouraging students to evaluate the values and outcomes of freedom,
19 constitutional republics, and human dignity.
20 C. The State Department of Education, in consultation with
21 experts in political history and education, shall develop and
22 implement high-quality professional learning opportunities for
23 educators tasked with teaching the atrocities of communism.
