1 D. For the purposes of this section, "communism" refers to a
2 political and economic ideology advocating for a classless society
3 under state-controlled means of production, historically leading to
4 authoritarian governance, widespread oppression, and mass
5 atrocities, as seen in regimes such as the Soviet Union, the
6 People’s Republic of China, Cuba, Cambodia, and others.
7 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
